==English==
===Adverb===
'''alright'''

#Alternative form of [[all right]] (but see '''Usage note''' below).

====Usage note====
Many people consider ''all right'' to be the only acceptable spelling and ''alright'' to be incorrect, formed by inappropriate analogy with [[already]].  However, the spelling ''alright'' is widespread (generating 2,280,000 hits on Google&reg; at the time of writing [20 March 2004] in comparison to 6,200,000 hits for ''all right'' [note however that some of the hits for '''all right''' will not be in the sense of this phrase given here; for example, in "I answered all of the questions in the exam and got them all right." ''all right'' means ''all correct'' rather than any of the definitions given under [[all right]]]).